metadata.name: ascii battles 2 #36
metadata.description:
Orcs Vs Kobold clash again each with a new ally. Giants join the orcs, throwing boulders and making big swing attacks. Demons join the kobolds, igniting enemies on fire and raising the dead. New maps provide new tactics with destructive terrain. Ascii carnage like you've never seen. Each map is newly generated every round. Random variation in army numbers gives each side a fighting chance.

MAPS: Swamp, Cave, Courtyard, Arena, Forest
Orcs: Orc warriors, Orc Wizards, Giants
Kobolds: Kobold warriors, Kobold throwers, Demons

metadata.name: Anachronous #207
metadata.description:
This project is about the exploration of chaotic structures created with lines and blurry silhouettes. They work together to make the shapes emerge without revealing them completely and create dark and light areas that compose a feeling of depth and weight to the scene.

Some pieces are chaotic, some more ordered. Some have strong compositions, some don't. By zooming in on the details we can let our mind wander and start seeing shapes.

Best experienced in full-screen.

Press S to take a screenshot
Press M to take a high resolution screenshot
Press H to take a higher resolution screenshot (may not work for some devices)

WARNING: Project is using webgl, it may not work on some older devices.

Original artwork by William Watkins ¬∑ Lyon, 2022

metadata.name: partition() #128
metadata.description:
This token continuously partitions the canvas, sometimes taking minutes to create tens of thousands of subdivisions. Each token has unique properties that govern partition number and shape, and a random chance to freeze a partition. This allows for a wide variety of outputs, all driven by pure randomness.

Properties describe the entropy of the final output, the final number of partitions, and a rare small chance for filled partitions. This token also has a few interactive features as well (see below).

Software | p5.js
Created  | 11/30/21
Artist   | nicthib

Controls:
1-9: Displays the construction of the piece at each iteration
p: Save a png of the current canvas
s: Save an svg of the current canvas (Note: this can break the live sketch, so reload the page if you want to interact further)
Space: Resets animation
Scroll, click/drag: zoom/pan

metadata.name: Dither_Graffiti #58
metadata.description:
With this token you can mint a series of each-time unique, pixel-dither graffiti-like compositions, put together via an algorithm that is randomly ‚Äúshuffling‚Äù the [pre-prepared] animated GIFs, background images and sometimes colours. 
The GIFs are chaotic hand-drawn doodles - some abstract, some asemic writing, mostly 1-bit monochromatic, with SOME colour ‚Äúspray paints‚Äù here and there ;^) 

Enjoy! 

___
Project by V5MT, 2022.
Technical Advisor: pifragile.

metadata.name: CityScape: Istanbul #88
metadata.description:
Istanbul is a city that straddles the Bosporus Strait, and lies in both Europe and Asia, with a population of over 15 million residents. Most of the population is located in big iconic hills known as the "Seven Hills of Istanbul". 

   In this project, I tried to capture and interpret the daily life routine of the people who live in these hills with the viewing point from Bosphorus. There are three camera angle possibilities to examine the details in different layers. Also, building types, the slope of the hill, and green area density vary in between those scenarios. There are two time zones: day and night. In the night scene, there is a possibility to obtain the crescent moon which is the symbol of the culture inhabits in these lands.

To save as a high-quality image, open in live view and click yes on the incoming prompt.

Created with p5js
